race.comment: KAMCHATKA (5) doesn't win out of turn but left a good impression last time out when beaten a neck into second over 1000m at this track. Should settle handy in the run and has a bit more improvement to come than a number of these. INFINITE MATRIX (1) finished third at Werribee two runs back but was less effective last time over 1100m at Seymour, finishing 6 lengths back in eighth. This looks infinitely easier, though, so a better showing is on the cards. BRONCO REVOLUTION (10) has been mixing form but was a winner three back and beaten just over a length here last time in a race no tougher than this. DENSETSU (4) might be the best of Andrew Dale's big team off a nice win last start at Holbrook.
